        "```{=latex}\n",
        "\\noindent\n",
        "\\begin{minipage}[t]{0.72\\textwidth}\n",
        "\\vspace{0pt}\n",
        "\\centering\n",
        "\\refstepcounter{figure}\\label{fig-reward-plot}\n",
        "\\includegraphics[width=\\linewidth]{cache/computedraft/v1/rl2_masked_v4/report_exports/plots/section4_reward_plot_inline.png}\n",
        "\\end{minipage}\\hfill\n",
        "\\begin{minipage}[t]{0.24\\textwidth}\n",
        "\\vspace{0pt}\n",
        "Figure~\\ref{fig-reward-plot} demonstrates the difference between the latent and observed rewards for individual participants with high and medium missingness. We see that the estimated latent reward is always greater than the observed reward. There is a larger difference for the participant with high missingness. This is expected because it is a sum of hourly buckets, for which many of the observations are missing.\n",
        "\\end{minipage}\n",
        "```"
